sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser as User Browser
    participant AuthProxy as kube-auth-proxy<br/>4180/TCP HTTP or 443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OIDCProv as OIDC Provider<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant OAuthSrv as OpenShift OAuth Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant OSApi as OpenShift API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Upstream as Upstream Application<br/>Configurable

    Note over Browser,Upstream: Flow 1: OIDC Authentication (auth mode)
    Browser->>AuthProxy: GET /* (unauthenticated)<br/>No credentials
    AuthProxy->>Browser: 302 Redirect to /oauth2/start
    Browser->>AuthProxy: GET /oauth2/start
    AuthProxy->>Browser: 302 Redirect to OIDC Provider
    Browser->>OIDCProv: Login page<br/>TLS 1.2+
    OIDCProv->>Browser: 302 Redirect with auth code
    Browser->>AuthProxy: GET /oauth2/callback?code=...<br/>Authorization code
    AuthProxy->>OIDCProv: POST token endpoint<br/>Client credentials (code exchange)
    OIDCProv-->>AuthProxy: ID Token + Access Token
    AuthProxy->>Upstream: Forward request<br/>User headers injected (X-Forwarded-*)
    Upstream-->>AuthProxy: Response
    AuthProxy-->>Browser: Response + Set-Cookie (session)

    Note over Browser,Upstream: Flow 2: OpenShift OAuth Authentication (auth mode)
    Browser->>AuthProxy: GET /* (unauthenticated)
    AuthProxy->>OAuthSrv: GET /.well-known/oauth-authorization-server<br/>Discovery
    OAuthSrv-->>AuthProxy: OAuth metadata
    AuthProxy->>Browser: 302 Redirect to OpenShift OAuth
    Browser->>OAuthSrv: Login page<br/>TLS 1.2+, User credentials
    OAuthSrv->>Browser: 302 Redirect with auth code
    Browser->>AuthProxy: GET /oauth2/callback?code=...
    AuthProxy->>OAuthSrv: POST token endpoint<br/>Client credentials (code exchange)
    OAuthSrv-->>AuthProxy: Access Token
    AuthProxy->>OSApi: GET /apis/user.openshift.io/v1/users/~<br/>Bearer Token
    OSApi-->>AuthProxy: User info
    AuthProxy->>Upstream: Forward request<br/>User headers injected
    Upstream-->>AuthProxy: Response
    AuthProxy-->>Browser: Response + Set-Cookie

    participant Client as API Client
    participant RBACProxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>Configurable/HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant UpstreamRBAC as Upstream Application

    Note over Client,UpstreamRBAC: Flow 3: Kubernetes RBAC Authorization (rbac mode)
    Client->>RBACProxy: HTTPS request<br/>Bearer Token or Client Certificate
    RBACProxy->>K8sAPI: TokenReview<br/>Service Account Token
    K8sAPI-->>RBACProxy: User identity
    RBACProxy->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>Service Account Token
    K8sAPI-->>RBACProxy: Allowed/Denied
    RBACProxy->>UpstreamRBAC: Forward (if authorized)<br/>Auth headers injected
    UpstreamRBAC-->>RBACProxy: Response
    RBACProxy-->>Client: Response

    participant Envoy as Envoy Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+

    Note over Envoy,Upstream: Flow 4: Envoy ext_authz Integration
    Browser->>Envoy: HTTPS request<br/>Cookie/Bearer
    Envoy->>AuthProxy: GET /oauth2/auth<br/>HTTP/4180 (pod-to-pod)<br/>Cookie/Bearer forwarded
    AuthProxy-->>Envoy: 200 (allow) or 401 (deny)
    Envoy->>Upstream: Forward (if allowed)<br/>Forwarded credentials
    Upstream-->>Envoy: Response
    Envoy-->>Browser: Response
